headline: 3 Industrials Stocks Walking a Fine Line
summary: Industrials businesses quietly power the physical things we depend on, from cars and homes to e-commerce infrastructure. Still, their generally high capital requirements expose them to the ups and downs of economic cycles, and the market seems to be baking in a prolonged downturn as the industry has shed 20.6% over the past six months. This performance was worse than the S&P 500’s 12.8% fall.
